sentences: Amanda Röntgen-Maier (20 February 1853 – 15 July 1894) was a Swedish violinist and composer.
She was the first female graduate in music direction from the Royal College of Music in Stockholm in 1872.
Her violin concerto was premiered in 1875 with Maier as soloist and received good reviews.
In Leipzig she met the German-Dutch pianist and composer Julius Röntgen (1855–1932), her violin teacher's son.
The couple married in 1880 in Landskrona and moved to Amsterdam.
In the late 1870s Maier also met Ethel Smyth, who was studying in Leipzig.
In 1887 Röntgen-Maier became ill with tuberculosis.
Her final major composition was the piano quartet in E minor on a trip to Norway in 1891.
She died in 1894 in Amsterdam, the Netherlands.
Sonata in B Minor for Violin and Piano (Publisher: Musikaliska Konstföreningen, Stockholm, 1878)
Six Pieces for Piano and Violin (Publisher: Breitkopf & Hartel, Leipzig, 1879)
Dialogues: Small Piano Pieces (with Julius Röntgen, Publisher: Breitkopf & Hartel, Leipzig, 1882)
String Quartet in A major (1877 – completed by B. Tommy Andersson in 2018)
String Quartet in A major (1877 – completed by B. Tommy Andersson in 2018)
In 2018 a string quartet was formed by members the Royal Stockholm Philharmonic Orchestra, and named the Maier Quartet.
